## IMPROVEMENT 3 — SNAP TO GRID

### 3.1 Grid system

Canvas: 1920 × 1080px
Default grid: 40px (48 columns × 27 rows)
Fine grid: 20px (96 × 54)
Coarse grid: 80px (24 × 13.5)

Grid is a coordinate system — it affects:
- Element positioning in agent tool calls
- Manual drag positioning in the asset overlay
- Sticker/image placement
- Text label positioning

### 3.2 Grid configuration

```ts
interface GridConfig {
  enabled: boolean        // default true
  size: 20 | 40 | 80     // px, default 40
  showGrid: boolean       // visual grid overlay, default false
  snapThreshold: number   // px distance to snap, default 12
  snapToElements: boolean // also snap to other elements' edges, default true
}
```

Add to GlobalStyle. Store in project settings.

### 3.3 Snap function

```ts
function snapToGrid(
  value: number,
  gridSize: number,
  threshold: number = 12
): number {
  const snapped = Math.round(value / gridSize) * gridSize;
  // Only snap if within threshold
  return Math.abs(value - snapped) <= threshold ? snapped : value;
}

function snapPoint(
  x: number,
  y: number,
  grid: GridConfig,
  otherElements?: Array<{ x: number, y: number, w: number, h: number }>
): { x: number, y: number, snappedX: boolean, snappedY: boolean } {
  let sx = x, sy = y;
  let snappedX = false, snappedY = false;
  
  if (grid.enabled) {
    const nx = snapToGrid(x, grid.size, grid.snapThreshold);
    const ny = snapToGrid(y, grid.size, grid.snapThreshold);
    if (nx !== x) { sx = nx; snappedX = true; }
    if (ny !== y) { sy = ny; snappedY = true; }
  }
  
  // Snap to other elements' edges
  if (grid.snapToElements && otherElements) {
    for (const el of otherElements) {
      // Check proximity to element edges
      const edges = {
        left: el.x, right: el.x + el.w,
        top: el.y, bottom: el.y + el.h,
        centerX: el.x + el.w/2, centerY: el.y + el.h/2,
      };
      
      for (const [, edge] of Object.entries(edges)) {
        if (Math.abs(sx - edge) < grid.snapThreshold) {
          sx = edge; snappedX = true;
        }
        if (Math.abs(sy - edge) < grid.snapThreshold) {
          sy = edge; snappedY = true;
        }
      }
    }
  }
  
  return { x: sx, y: sy, snappedX, snappedY };
}
```

### 3.4 Visual snap feedback

When dragging and snapping, show:
- Snap lines: thin red lines extending across canvas
  at the snapped x or y position
- Snap indicator: small red dot at snap point
