### 5.6 Template instantiation

When a template is selected:
1. Deep copy the template layers (generate new IDs)
2. Prompt the agent to fill in placeholders based on context:
   "Fill in this template for a scene about: [user's prompt]"
   Agent replaces ${TITLE}, ${BODY} etc with appropriate content
3. Apply the scene's style override
4. Write scene HTML
5. Preview shows the instantiated template

```ts
async function instantiateTemplate(
  template: SceneTemplate,
  userPrompt: string,
  style: GlobalStyle
): Promise<Scene> {
  // Generate placeholder values
  const placeholderValues = await fillPlaceholders(
    template.placeholders,
    userPrompt,
    style
  );
  
  // Clone layers with new IDs and filled placeholders
  const layers = template.layers.map(layer => ({
    ...layer,
    id: generateId(),
    generatedCode: replacePlaceholders(
      layer.generatedCode,
      placeholderValues
    ),
  }));
  
  return {
    id: generateId(),
    name: userPrompt.slice(0, 40),
    duration: template.duration,
    layers,
    styleOverride: template.styleOverride,
    bgColor: template.styleOverride.bgColor ?? style.bgColor,
    thumbnail: null,
    interactions: [],
    audioLayer: null,
    videoLayer: null,
    transition: { type: 'none', duration: 0.5 },
  };
}
```

