## PART 6 — INTEGRATION POINTS

### 6.1 How these five improvements work together

**Scrubbing + Parenting:**
When scrubbing, the time resolver must use absolute start times
(accounting for parent offsets) to correctly show which elements
are visible at each frame.

**Snap + Agent:**
Agent tool calls normalize coordinates through snapToGrid()
automatically. User never has to specify exact pixel coords.

**Style Presets + Templates:**
Templates can specify a style preset. When instantiated,
the scene gets that preset. User can then override further.

**Templates + Agent:**
Director agent can plan a video using templates for structure
scenes and generate custom layers for content scenes.
Mix-and-match: template gives the layout, agent fills the content.

**Scrubbing + Layer Parenting:**
Frame-stepper shows which layers are active at current frame.
Highlight active layers in the layer panel as you scrub.
Parent/child timing relationships visible in the layer panel.

### 6.2 Layer panel active state while scrubbing

When currentTime > 0 (scrubbing), highlight layers that are
active at currentTime in the layer panel:

```tsx
function isLayerActiveAtTime(
  layer: SceneLayer,
  time: number,
  allLayers: SceneLayer[],
  sceneDuration: number
): boolean {
  const absStart = getAbsoluteStartAt(layer, allLayers);
  const end = layer.duration !== null
    ? absStart + layer.duration
    : sceneDuration;
  return time >= absStart && time <= end;
}
```

Active layers get a green left border in the layer list.
Inactive (not yet started or already finished) get gray opacity.

