## CRITICAL NOTES

Scrub performance: reloading the iframe on every scrub event
is expensive. Debounce seek to 50ms — only reload when user
stops dragging for 50ms. During the drag, show the scrub
position visually but don't reload the iframe until settled.

Seek + Canvas2D: the skip-waits approach means all canvas2d
content renders instantly at seek time. This is correct behavior
but fast — the iframe may flash blank for 100ms while the
instant render completes. Add a 100ms transition on iframe opacity
to hide this flash.

Template placeholders: when extracting placeholders from a
user's scene to save as template, don't automatically extract
everything. Show the user a list of detected strings and let
them choose which to mark as placeholders. Over-templating
makes templates too generic.

Layer parenting cycles: before executing set_layer_parent,
validate no cycles exist. Walk up the parent chain from the
proposed parent — if you reach the child's id, it's a cycle.
Reject with a clear error message in chat.

Grid snap + agent: the agent should still specify semantically
meaningful coordinates ("center of canvas = 960, 540") not
just any multiple of 40. Snapping is a polish layer, not
a substitute for spatial reasoning. Inject the grid size
but also inject semantic zone descriptions.

Style presets in HTML: when scene HTML is generated, use
resolveSceneStyle() to get the effective palette/font/etc
for that scene. The PALETTE constant in the HTML file
reflects the resolved style, not the global style.
This ensures chalkboard scenes get white strokes etc.
```